'''Jiangxi province''' was a province of the [[Yuan dynasty]] established in 1277. It included modern [[Jiangxi]], and most of [[Guangdong]].<ref>Duosang Mongol History, Vol. 1; Zhong-gou Tong-shi; History of Zhong-gou Border Nationalities; The New Yuan-shih</ref> The capital was [[Longxing]], now called [[Nanchang]].

'''Queen's Wharf''' is a multipurpose entertainment and hotel precinct straddling [[William Street, Brisbane|William Street]], under construction  in the [[Brisbane central business district|Brisbane CBD]] of Queensland, Australia. The redevelopment will include the construction of five new high-rise buildings and the repurposing of existing heritage-listed structures within the site.
